==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decanal
<hw>Dec"a*nal</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧canal</ets>. See <er>Dean</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to
a dean or deanery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His rectorial as well as <qex>decanal</qex> residence.</q>
<rj><qau>Churton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Decanal side</b></col>, <cd>the side of the choir on
which the dean's tall is placed.</cd> -- <col><b>Decanal
stall</b></col>, <cd>the stall allotted to the dean in the choir, on the
right or south side of the chancel.</cd>
<rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decandria</ent>⟦br⟧
